    "causal_summary": "Per-seed CocoIndex fork telemetry passthrough (rawScore, pathClass, rankingSignals) on code_graph_context anchors. Closes Q-OPP from research.md §6 and Novel Finding #5 from 010 stress test. The fork (cocoindex_code v0.2.3+spec-kit-fork.0.2.0) emits these fields per QueryResult; previously code_graph_context dropped them when accepting CocoIndex seeds, losing audit and explanation provenance. This packet extends the seed schema (snake_case + camelCase), normalizes wire names, propagates fields through resolveCocoIndexSeed, and conditionally emits them on returned anchors. Pure additive metadata: anchor score, confidence, resolution, source, and ordering remain byte-equal pre vs post on a fixed fixture corpus. Excludes any change to mcp_server/lib/search/* (research.md §6.3 alt #3 REJECTED — would double-apply the fork's path_class signal). Excludes the response-level dedupedAliases / uniqueResultCount counters (research.md §6.3 alt #2 deferred).",
